<main class="section container">
  <h1>Wooden Bridge (IDP1)</h1>
  <p class="section-sub">Cohort-best load test: <strong>2.4 kN</strong> (pass requirement: 1.1 kN)</p>

  <img src="../assets/bridge.jpg" alt="Bridge project" style="width:100%;height:auto;border-radius:16px;border:1px solid var(--grey-2)">

  <h2>Brief</h2>
  <p>Design and build a wooden bridge to meet a minimum load requirement with constraints on materials and dimensions.</p>

  <h2>Approach</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Selected truss configuration to maximise stiffness-to-mass.</li>
    <li>Prioritised glue joints and load paths to reduce stress concentrations.</li>
    <li>Built and tested with a two-person team due to limited availability.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Results</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Withstood <strong>2.4 kN</strong> — highest in cohort.</li>
    <li>Exceeded pass requirement (1.1 kN) with significant safety margin.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Lessons</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Joint quality and geometry selection dominate performance in lightweight structures.</li>
    <li>Lean team ⇒ faster iteration and clearer ownership.</li>
  </ul>
</main>

